	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree that the player (not character) earned the suit, and I can also understand passing back and forth between characters (which a guildmate is a great help as they can act as an honourable middleman if required).... indeed I agree with almost all of your statements save the poor cleric one (grin). <br><br>Having now gotten to L34 and started getting my class armour, I can see a point where Cleric funds start to increase if you can restrain from purchasing the "latest and greatest" items (as well as skills like Blacksmithing).<br><br>Try and save up 1000 pp for the platinum you'll need for the class armour. In my case I'm choosing not to go for the mace and the shield (I've a testement of Vaniir (sic)), and going to do the bracers twice. After you accumulate that large amount of pp, and are about L35, that armour will see you through until :<br>a) You go Planar (which I doubt I will, too small a guild)<br>b) You go Dragon or Kunark or Velous<br>and the replacement items will be from kills and, in theory, no cost. Always save for your next spell level (about 200 pp at L34) (?250 300 odd L39), and you will find that you will get through that cash crunch. What to do with your money once you have the class armour and money for the next spell level? Then you can start to purchase things that you "want", but either don't have time to go get, or not enough time to get it. I've seen Forest loops go from 1200 pp down to 600 pp.... this over a 3 month time. The longer you can put it off, the less expensive it can become. It requires a bit of sacrifice now, but can pay off in the future, and who knows? there might be a "new" item that makes the latest and greatest items look like cheap trash (grin)<br><br>I do plan to carry on with my smithing skill (Dwarven racial armour + Imbue Ruby = +wisdom armour), but that will be at L38+ when the cash crunch will be done. <br><br>The symbol spells as cash sink? Cast only when necessary and, if needed, don't stint them as a good group will get you platinum, and a bad group will get you to use the old heel-toe express for CR....<br><br>May you get your Donals!<br><br>Durus Stoneguard<br>Initiate of the 34th Mystery of Brell Serilis<br>Povar<br><br>(Who is currently helping a ranger of his guild do his class armour, and realizes that Clerics have it alright... a Skull of Meldrath? ick)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
